CatDescriptText: Margaret Strawder, college student, Homewood was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, July 28, 1962, pg. 15 with question: "When do you think the Pirates will move into first place?"  Answer reads: "I don't think they'll really have a chance this year.  They're not doing any better than they did last year."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of man wearing geometric patterned button down collared shirt and cap, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of Margaret Strawder wearing sunglasses and striped button down collared shirt and brooch, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
